data.text: Malawi, officially named the Republic of Malawi, it’s a country located in the southwest of Africa. It is bordered by Zambia to the northwest, Tanzania to the northeast and Mozambique on the east, south, and west. Malawi is separated from Tanzania and Mozambique by Lake Malawi. Malawi is over 118,000 KM2 and it has an estimated population of 18,977,913. The capital is Lilongwe which happens to be the Malawi’s largest city.
